.TH FLATC "1" "January 2025" "" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
.B flatc
\(en FlatBuffers compiler
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B flatc
.RI [\  GENERATOR_OPTIONS \ ]
.RB [\  \-o\ \fIPATH \ ]
.IR FILES ...
.RB [\  \-\-\ \fIBINARY_FILES  ...\ ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The main compiler for FlatBuffers is called
.BR flatc (1)
and is used to convert schema definitions into generated code files
for a variety of languages.
.SH OPTIONS
.IP \(bu 2
The
.I GENERATOR_OPTIONS
specify the language(s) to compile code for
as well as various features to enable/disable.
.IP \(bu 2
The
.B \-o\ \fIPATH
specifies the path where the generated files are placed.
It defaults to the current path if not specified.
.IP \(bu 2
The
.B \-I\ \fIPATH
specifies the path where included schema files are located.
It defaults to the current path if not specified.
.SS "INPUT FILES"
\fIFILES\fR... specifies one or more schema or data files to process.
They are processed in the order provided.
.SS "SCHEMA FILES"
For schema files, language specifiers indicate
what languages to generate code for.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-cpp :
C++
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-java :
Java
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-kotlin :
Kotlin
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-csharp :
C#
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-go :
Golang
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-python :
Python
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-js :
JavaScript
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-ts :
TypeScript
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-php :
PHP
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-dart :
Dart
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-lua :
Lua
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-lobster :
Lobster
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-rust :
Rust
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-swift :
Swift
.IP \(bu 2
.BR \-\-nim :
Nim
.PD
.P
Additionally, adding
.B \-\-grpc
will generate RPC stub code for gRPC (not available in all languages).
.SS "DATA FILES"
If \fIFILES\fR... contain data files,
they can be exported to either a binary or JSON representation.
.TP
.B \-\-binary\fR, \fB\-b\fR
Generate a binary file containing a serialized flatbuffer.
.PD 0
.TP
.B \-\-json\fR, \fB\-j\fR
Generate JSON file from a serialized flatbuffer.
.PD
.P
Both options require the corresponding schema file to be included first
in the list of \fIFILES\fR....
.TP
.B To Binary
To serialize the JSON data in
.B mydata.json
using the schema
.BR myschema.fbs :
.RS +3n
.IP
.EX
.B flatc --binary myschema.fbs mydata.json
.EE
.RE
.IP
This will generate a
.B mydata_wire.bin
file containing the serialized flatbuffer data.
.TP
.B To JSON
To convert the serialized binary flatbuffer
.B mydata.bin
using the schema
.B myschema.fbs
to JSON:
.RS +3n
.IP
.EX
.B flatc --json myschema.fbs mydata.bin
.EE
.RE
.IP
This will generate a
.B mydata.json
file.
.SS "ADDITIONAL OPTIONS"
.TP
.B \-o\ \fIPATH
Output all generated files to
.I PATH
(either absolute, or relative to the current directory).
If omitted,
.I PATH
will be the current directory.
.I PATH
should end in your system\(cqs path separator,
e.g. \fB/\fR or \fB\\\fR.
.TP
.B \-I\ \fIPATH
When encountering
.B include
statements, attempt to load the files from this path.
Paths will be tried in the order given,
and if all fail (or none are specified)
it will try to load relative to the path
of the schema file being parsed.
.TP
.B \-M
Print make rules for generated files.
.TP
.B \-\-strict\-json
Require and generate strict JSON
(field names are enclosed in quotes,
no trailing commas in tables/vectors).
By default, no quotes are required/generated,
and trailing commas are allowed.
.TP
.B \-\-allow\-non\-utf8
Pass non-UTF-8 input through parser and emit nonstandard
.BI \\\\\\\\ x
escapes in JSON.
(Default is to raise parse error on non-UTF-8 input.)
.B \-\-natural\-utf8
Output strings with UTF-8 as human-readable strings.
By default, UTF-8 characters are printed as
.BI \\\\\\\\u XXXX
escapes.
.TP
.B \-\-defaults\-json
Output fields whose value is equal to the default value
when writing JSON text.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-prefix
Don\(cqt prefix enum values in generated C++ by their enum type.
.TP
.B \-\-scoped\-enums
Use C++11 style scoped and strongly typed enums in generated C++.
This also implies
.BR \-\-no\-prefix .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-emit\-min\-max\-enum\-values
Disable generation of
.B MIN
and
.B MAX
enumerated values for scoped enums and prefixed enums.
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-includes
.RI ( deprecated )
This is the default behavior.
If the original behavior is required (no
.B include
statements) use
.BR \-\-no\-includes.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-includes
Don\(cqt generate include statements for included schemas
the generated file depends on (C++ / Python).
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-mutable
Generate additional non-const accessors
for mutating FlatBuffers in-place.
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-onefile
Generate single output file for C#, Go, and Python.
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-name\-strings
Generate type name functions for C++.
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-object\-api
Generate an additional object-based API.
This API is more convenient for object construction and mutation
than the base API, at the cost of efficiency (object allocation).
Recommended only to be used if other options are insufficient.
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-compare
Generate
.B operator==
for object-based API types.
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-nullable
Add Clang
.B _Nullable
for C++ pointer or
.B @Nullable
for Java.
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-generated
Add
.B @Generated
annotation for Java.
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-jvmstatic
Add
.B @JvmStatic
annotation for Kotlin methods in companion object
for interop from Java to Kotlin.
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-all
Generate not just code for the current schema files,
but for all files it includes as well.
If the language uses a single file for output
(by default the case for C++ and JS),
all code will end up in this one file.
.TP
.B \-\-cpp\-include
Adds an
.B #include
in generated file.
.TP
.B \-\-cpp\-ptr\-type\ \fIT
Set object API pointer type
(default
.BR std::unique_ptr )
.TP
.B \-\-cpp\-str\-type\ \fIT
Set object API string type
(default
.BR std::string ).
.IB T ::c_str()\fR,
.IB T ::length()
and
.IB T ::empty()
must be supported.
The custom type also needs to be constructible from
.B std::string
(see the
.B \-\-cpp\-str\-flex\-ctor
option to change this behavior).
.TP
.B \-\-cpp\-str\-flex\-ctor
Don\(cqt construct custom string types by passing
.B std::string
from Flatbuffers, but
.BR (char*\ +\ length) .
This allows efficient construction of custom string types,
including zero-copy construction.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cpp\-direct\-copy
Don\(cqt generate direct copy methods for C++ object-based API.
.TP
.B \-\-cpp\-std\ \fICPP_STD
Generate a C++ code using features of selected C++ standard.
Supported
.I CPP_STD
values:
.PD 0
.RS +10n
.IP \(bu 2n
.B c++0x
\(en generate code compatible with old compilers (VS2010),
.IP \(bu 2n
.B c++11
\(en use C++11 code generator
.RI ( default ),
.IP \(bu 2n
.B c++17
\(en use C++17 features in generated code
.RI ( experimental ).
.RE
.PD
.TP
.B \-\-object\-prefix
Customise class prefix for C++ object-based API.
.TP
.B \-\-object\-suffix
Customise class suffix for C++ object-based API.
.TP
.B \-\-go\-namespace
Generate the overrided namespace in Golang.
.TP
.B \-\-go\-import
Generate the overrided import for flatbuffers in Golang.
(default is
.BR "github.com/google/flatbuffers/go" ).
.TP
.B \-\-raw\-binary
Allow binaries without a
.B file_indentifier
to be read.
This may crash
.BR flatc (1)
given a mismatched schema.
.TP
.B \-\-size\-prefixed
Input binaries are size prefixed buffers.
.TP
.B \-\-proto
Expect input files to be
.B .proto
files (protocol buffers).
Output the corresponding
.B .fbs
file.
Currently supports:
.BR package ,
.BR message ,
.BR enum ,
nested declarations,
.B import
(use
.B \-I
for paths),
.BR extend ,
.BR oneof ,
.BR group .
Does not support, but will skip without error:
.BR option ,
.BR service ,
.BR extensions ,
and most everything else.
.TP
.B \-\-oneof\-union
Translate
.B .proto
.BR oneof s
to flatbuffer unions.
.TP
.B \-\-grpc
Generate GRPC interfaces for the specified languages.
.TP
.B \-\-schema
Serialize schemas instead of JSON (use with
.BR \-b ).
This will output a binary version of the specified schema
that itself corresponds to the
.BR reflection / reflection.fbs
schema.
Loading this binary file is the basis for reflection functionality.
.TP
.B \-\-bfbs\-comments
Add doc comments to the binary schema files.
.TP
.B \-\-conform\ \fIFILE
Specify a schema the following schemas should be an evolution of.
Gives errors if not.
Useful to check if schema modifications don\(cqt break
schema evolution rules.
.TP
.B \-\-conform\-includes\ \fIPATH
Include path for the schema given with
.BR \-\-conform\ \fIPATH .
.TP
.B \-\-filename\-suffix\ \fISUFFIX
The suffix appended to the generated file names.
Default is
.BR _generated .
.TP
.B \-\-filename\-ext\ \fIEXTENSION
The extension appended to the generated file names.
Default is language-specific (e.g. \fB"h"\fR for C++).
This should not be used when multiple languages are specified.
.TP
.B \-\-include\-prefix\ \fIPATH
Prefix this path to any generated include statements.
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-prefix
Keep original prefix of schema include statement.
.TP
.B \-\-reflect\-types
Add minimal type reflection to code generation.
.TP
.B \-\-reflect\-names
Add minimal type/name reflection.
.TP
.B \-\-root\-type\ \fIT
Select or override the default
.BR root_type .
.TP
.B \-\-require\-explicit\-ids
When parsing schemas, require explicit ids
.RB ( id:\ \fIx ).
.TP
.B \-\-force\-defaults
Emit default values in binary output from JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-force\-empty
When serializing from object API representation,
force strings and vectors to empty rather than null.
.TP
.B \-\-force\-empty\-vectors
When serializing from object API representation,
force vectors to empty rather than null.
.TP
.B \-\-flexbuffers
Used with
.B \-\-binary
and
.B \-\-json
options,
it generates data using schema-less FlexBuffers.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-warnings
Inhibit all warning messages.
.TP
.B \-\-cs\-global\-alias
Prepend
.B global::
to all user generated csharp classes and structs.
.TP
.B \-\-json\-nested\-bytes
Allow a
.B nested_flatbuffer
field to be parsed as a vector of bytes in JSON,
which is unsafe unless checked by a verifier afterwards.
.TP
.B \-\-python\-no\-type\-prefix\-suffix
Skip emission of Python functions that are prefixed with typenames.
.TP
.B \-\-python\-typing
Generate Python type annotations.
.SS "ADDITIONAL gRPC OPTIONS"
.TP
.B \-\-grpc\-filename\-suffix
.BI [ C++ ]
An optional suffix for the generated files\(cq names.
For example, compiling gRPC for C++ with
.B \-\-grpc\-filename\-suffix=.fbs
will generate
.RI { name }\fB.fbs.h
and
.RI { name }\fB.fbs.cc
files.
.TP
.B \-\-grpc\-additional\-header
.BI [ C++ ]
Additional headers to include in the generated files.
.TP
.B \-\-grpc\-search\-path
.BI [ C++ ]
An optional prefix for the gRPC runtime path.
For example, compiling gRPC for C++ with
.B \-\-grpc\-search\-path=some/path
will generate the following includes:
.RS +3n
.IP
.EX
.B #include\ "some/path/grpcpp/impl/codegen/async_stream.h"
.B #include\ "some/path/grpcpp/impl/codegen/async_unary_call.h"
.B #include\ "some/path/grpcpp/impl/codegen/method_handler.h"
.B ...\:
.EE
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-grpc\-use\-system\-headers
.BI [ C++ ]
Whether to generate
.B #include\ <header>
instead of
.B #include\ "header.h"
for all headers when compiling gRPC for C++.
For example, compiling gRPC for C++ with
.B \-\-grpc\-use\-system\-headers
will generate the following includes:
.RS +3n
.IP
.EX
.B #include\ <some/path/grpcpp/impl/codegen/async_stream.h>
.B #include\ <some/path/grpcpp/impl/codegen/async_unary_call.h>
.B #include\ <some/path/grpcpp/impl/codegen/method_handler.h>
.B ...\:
.EE
.RE
.IP
.IR NOTE :
This option can be negated with
.BR \-\-no\-grpc\-use\-system\-headers .
.TP
.B \-\-grpc\-python\-typed\-handlers
.BI [ Python ]
Whether to generate the typed handlers that use the generated
Python classes instead of raw bytes for requests/responses.
.SH NOTES
Short-form options for generators are deprecated;
use the long form whenever possible.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.UR https://google.github.io/flatbuffers
Official documentation
.UE
